      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i drive it i keep hearing this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if i messed up or if it's a sensor or a stuck caliper. what do u think?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you might have a few possibilities causing that high-pitched squeal. Sometimes, the brake pads aren't seated perfectly, or there might be a slight issue with the new pads themselves, especially if they are a different material than the old ones. It could also be a piece of dust or debris caught between the rotor and the new pad. Have you checked that all the hardware, like the shims or clips, is properly installed? If the noise persists after a short break-in period, a mechanic should take a look to check for caliper alignment or sensor issues.",
      "source": "target",
