      "content": "A random, high-pitched sound that changes location can sometimes be caused by foreign material, like a tiny piece of grit, lodged between the pad and the rotor. If the noise is genuinely scraping metal-on-metal, that requires immediate inspection, as it suggests significant wear or binding. Since you can't pinpoint the wheel, a visual inspection of all four rotors and pads would be necessary to diagnose if any are damaged or improperly seated. It's wise to have it checked soon to ensure the braking system is fully operational and safe.",
